snippet.title: CarnivoryCon2019: Dr. Paul Mason — “From Lupus to Diabetes: How Your Diet Can Impact Autoimmune..."
snippet.description:
Dr Paul Mason is a credentialed Sports and Exercise Medicine Physician, having obtained his medical degree with honors from the University of Sydney. He also holds  degrees in Physiotherapy and Occupational Health. Dr Mason has long experience with low carbohydrate and ketogenic diets, both personally and professionally. He has utilised ketogenic diets successfully both in the general public and for elite athletes. 

He has spent an enormous amount of time understanding nutrition research, and is not afraid to diverge from conventional wisdom when dictated by the available evidence. This includes challenging many of the pillars of contemporary dietary advice, including on fat, salt and fibre intake. His most recent interest is the impact of diet on autoimmune conditions.
